{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"Overview","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"üí∞ If you‚Äôre looking for a reliable and secure way to license your work, look no further than IRLLicence. Try it out today and ensure that your application or framework is fully licensed and secure!"}]},{"anchor":"About","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"About"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Welcome to "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/IRLLicence\/documentation\/IRLLicence\/IRLLicence"},{"type":"text","text":" ‚Äì a powerful code validation mechanism that ensures your binary is running where and how it is supposed to."}]},{"anchor":"üì¶-How-it-works","level":4,"type":"heading","text":"üì¶ How it works"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Integrate this library into your code"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Lock the functionalities or initialization of your code"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Verify your client‚Äôs license data \/ email"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The library will also ensure the App Bundle ID and email validated from the license are running inside the correct App Bundle ID."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Using "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/IRLLicence\/documentation\/IRLLicence"},{"type":"text","text":", you can easily prevent your code from being used by unauthorized parties."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The tool is built using Swift and supports Swift 5.4 and newer (swift-tools-version:5.7), making it easy to incorporate into your existing projects."}]},{"anchor":"üíÅ‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è-What-happens-as-a-client","level":4,"type":"heading","text":"üíÅ‚Äç‚ôÇÔ∏è What happens as a client"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Please note that as a client, you will need to use a license that is associated with the correct App Bundle ID."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The license is set to expire too. You must renew the license and publish your app at this stage."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The license is completely locked to you as a client and your email address. It is only valid for use with the App Bundle ID specified at the time of registration and until it expires."}]},{"anchor":"Getting-Started","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Getting Started"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Getting started with IRLLicence is easy. Simply add the code to your project, distribute your Framework or Application as a closed source, and lock your code to be usable only with a valid license and email. Once your client verifies the license, your code will be able to run with confidence, knowing that it is fully licensed and secure."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"IRLLicence primarily uses "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/swift.org\/package-manager\/"},{"type":"text","text":" as its build tool, so we recommend using that as well. If you want to depend on IRLLicence in your own project, it‚Äôs as simple as adding a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dependencies"},{"type":"text","text":" clause to your "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Package.swift"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["dependencies: [","    .package(url: \"https:\/\/github.com\/irlmob\/IRLLicence.git\", from: \"1.0.0\")","]"]},{"anchor":"Swift-54-and-newer-swift-tools-version57","level":4,"type":"heading","text":"Swift 5.4 and newer (swift-tools-version:5.7)"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["    dependencies: [.product(name: \"IRLLicence\", package: \"IRLLicence\") ]"]},{"anchor":"Using-Xcode-Package-support","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Using Xcode Package support"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If your project is set up as an Xcode project and you‚Äôre using Xcode 11+, you can add IRLLicence as a dependency to your"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Xcode project by clicking File -> Swift Packages -> Add Package Dependency. In the upcoming dialog, please enter"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"https:\/\/github.com\/irlmob\/IRLLicence.git"},{"type":"text","text":" and click Next twice. Finally, select the targets you are planning to use (here "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"IRLLicence"},{"type":"text","text":") and click finish. Now will be able to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"import IRLLicence"},{"type":"text","text":" (as well as all"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the other targets you have selected) in your project."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To work on IRLLicence itself, or to investigate some of the demonstration applications, you can check the Tests."}]},{"anchor":"Usage-example-Simple-validation","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"Usage example - Simple validation"},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["let licence = \"bVJkaVZEUXpVY<...>zQ5Mw==\"","let validator = try IRLLicence(email: \"notanemail@notanemail.com\", licence: licence,","publicKey: publicKey2048Base64)","let isValid = await validator.validate()","print(\"üîÑ Is Valid: \" + isValid ? \"‚úÖ YES\" : \"‚õîÔ∏è NO\")","print(\"‚úÖ Expire on: \\(validator.expire)\")"]},{"anchor":"MIT-License","level":2,"type":"heading","text":"MIT License"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/github.com\/irlmob\/IRLLicence\/blob\/main\/LICENSE"}]}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"